selocal
=======

The selocal script allows administrators to quickly manage locally added
SELinux policy rules.

Adding an allow / dontaudit / auditallow rule
---------------------------------------------

Example:
	selocal add allow mozilla_t self:process execmem

Removing a privilege
--------------------

Remove the privilege. Use the exact output as shown in the "selocal list".

Example:
	selocal del allow mozilla_t self:process { execmem };

Listing current privileges
--------------------------

Example:
	selocal list
